Dystar's RMP Executive Summary for the 

Resinbond K-250 Process





Overall approach to chemical safety. 



Dystar LP is committed to meeting and (or) exceeding all regulatory requirements in regards to Chemical Safety. Dystar has a comprehensive Environmental Health & Safety (EH&S) program that takes a proactive approach towards employee safety as well as the surrounding community. 



As part of the Senior management team, Dystar's Reidsville, NC location, Site Manager who answers directly to the President and CEO of Dystar is ultimately responsible for the EH&S programs at the covered process site. The Site Manager is intimately involved in all EH&S programs including Risk Management Planning (RMP) and Process Safety Management (PSM) and communicates all aspects of the EH&S programs to senior level management. 



Senior Management commitment provides the motivating force and resources for organization and controlling activities within Dystar's facilities.  Senior management must act as a role model for how all employees should work to &#8232;create a safe work environment. 

Dystar's Active Senior Management leadership includes:

?    Implementation of a comprehensive safety and health management program. &#8232;

?    Providing appropriate financial, human, and organizational resources to ensure a top-notch EH&S program is in place. &#8232;

?    Issuance of a written safety and health policy as a value of the organization as included in the Safety / Environmental Policy, Program, and Procedure Manual. &#8232;

?    Define roles, assigning responsibilities, establishing accountability and delegating authority. &#8232;

?    Integrate the safety and health goals' objectives into the organization's business systems and processes. &#8232;

?    Discuss safety and health processes and improvements regularly during staff or employee meetings. &#8232;

?    Ensure management is held accountable for accident-prevention processes. &#8232;

